@raulgonzm Sorry my answer wasn't clear. Yes, I did mean "correctly" - the shortcut to the view passes in the request by default, so that is fine. You can optionally remove it if you wish not to enforce the permissions on your schema by defining your own view. By omitting the request, all your routes will render, however, if you depend on the `request` object in your serializers, you may get some errors.

The docs on schema generation are here: http://www.django-rest-framework.org/api-guide/schemas/#using-an-explicit-schema-view

