@edmorley Hello, I was investigating an issue with our Django app running into occasional socket timeouts to our Memcache cluster. I believe it's caused by the issue you fixed in Django (https://code.djangoproject.com/ticket/11331), which you're porting to `django-pylibmc` in this PR.

When we deployed this fix, we actually saw a huge swell in connections to our Memcache cluster and lots of connection errors until we reverted. It sounds very similar to the issue described here: https://github.com/Cadasta/cadasta-platform/pull/1953

I'm wondering if you have any thoughts on what might cause this. I apologize for reaching out in this PR but I also wanted to note this as a word of warning for anyone porting this change to their app; there may be some library or condition that is causing `libmemcache` to not handle connections properly, and changing `close()` to no-op caused a connection leak on our servers.

